  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This resulted in a total of 5 326 931 and 3 272 525 reads, respectively covering 9772 fungal and 8142 bacterial OTUs for soil samples, and 10 511 905 and 23 407 319 reads, respectively covering 4322 fungal and 19 355 bacterial OTUs for root samples.",
    "Two soil 16S and ITS samples, four root 16S samples, and 24 root ITS samples yielded insufficient reads or failed to amplify and were excluded from further analysis.",
    "Fungal OTUs were subsequently assigned to a primary lifestyle at the genus level using the FungalTraits tool 29.",
    "In addition to the primary lifestyle alignments, we assigned a secondary lifestyle to potential DSE fungi (genus level) based on genera that contain species or strains with potential DSE capacity based on the category 'root endophytic capacity' in the FungalTraits tool (for a list of the potential DSE taxa used in this study see Supplementary Data 2).",
    "Shotgun metagenomic sequencing was performed on pooled equimolar amounts of DNA from five replicate soil and root samples per tree species per site."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Fungal OTUs were subsequently assigned to a primary lifestyle at the genus level using the FungalTraits tool 29."
  ]
